# NFS exports for student volumes
# Allow access from the Docker Swarm network (172.30.0.0/16)
#
# ⚠️  WARNING: DEVELOPMENT ONLY - INSECURE CONFIGURATION ⚠️
#
# This configuration uses insecure NFS options suitable ONLY for local development:
# - no_root_squash: Allows root user on client to have root access on server
# - insecure: Allows connections from ports above 1024
# - *: Wildcard export allows any host to mount (second line)
#
# NEVER use these settings in production!
#
# For production, use:
# - Replace wildcard (*) with specific IP ranges
# - Use root_squash instead of no_root_squash
# - Remove insecure option
# - Add all_squash with anonuid/anongid for better security
# - Configure proper firewall rules
# - Use sec=krb5 for Kerberos authentication if possible
#
# Example production config:
# /exports/student-volumes 10.0.0.0/24(rw,sync,no_subtree_check,root_squash,all_squash,anonuid=1000,anongid=1000,fsid=0)
#
/exports/student-volumes 172.30.0.0/16(rw,sync,no_subtree_check,no_root_squash,insecure,fsid=0)
/exports/student-volumes *(rw,sync,no_subtree_check,no_root_squash,insecure,fsid=0)
